adb_alias tool

Typically if you connect multiple Android devices on your Host PC
Then you can not use `adb` command directly and should use `adb -s serial` instead to access specific device
Which might be annoying

This tool help you to create adb alias to these devices easily

Usage:
set_adb_alias [SERIAL] [ALIAS]
    It will set alias 'adb_{ALIAS}' as 'adb -s {SERIAL}'
    example:
        $ set_adb_alias 11f7cd tango

    Then you can use 'adb_tango shell' to login device 11f7cd's shell
        $ adb_tangle shell

unset_adb_alias [ALIAS]
    It will unset alias you set prviously
    example:
        $ unset_adb_alias tango

show_adb_alias
    Show all alias you have set
